name: INStartAudioCallIntentHandling
desc: The handler interface for initiating an audio call from your app.DeprecatedUse INStartCallIntentHandling instead.

items.name: func resolveContacts(for: INStartAudioCallIntent, with: ([INPersonResolutionResult]) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the recipients of the call.

items.name: func resolveDestinationType(for: INStartAudioCallIntent, with: (INCallDestinationTypeResolutionResult) -> Void)
items.desc: Resolves the destination of the call.

items.name: func confirm(intent: INStartAudioCallIntent, completion: (INStartAudioCallIntentResponse) -> Void)
items.desc: Validates whether your app is able to initiate the call.

items.name: func handle(intent: INStartAudioCallIntent, completion: (INStartAudioCallIntentResponse) -> Void)
items.desc: Provides information to hand off the call to your app.
